===Noun===
'''cell wall'''
{{wikipedia}}

#(Biology)A thick, practically solid, layer forming around [[cell]]s of  [[bacteria]], [[Archaea]], [[fungi]], [[plant]]s, and [[algae]] (but not [[animal]]s and other [[protist]]s which generally have cell membranes without cell walls).  The cell wall serves a structural function helping the cell maintain its shape and protecting the cell from damage.


